<item>
            <title>[SPR-13035] Ability to prefix each RestTemplate request using some kind of UriPrefixingClientHttpRequestFactory</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-13035</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Please consider to provide some way how to prefix all requests from RestTemplate with the same basic prefix (usually protocol://host:port/someapiprefix form).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe this use case is pretty widespread as people uses RestTemplate to implement custom client libraries for apis, which resides on the same prefix quite often.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there already is such possibility, please point me the right direction. Otherwise I would love to cooperate on inclusion (and possible improvements) of our &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/martiner/gooddata-java/blob/master/src/main/java/com/gooddata/UriPrefixingClientHttpRequestFactory.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;UriPrefixingClientHttpRequestFactory&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/martiner/gooddata-java/blob/master/src/main/java/com/gooddata/UriPrefixer.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;UriPrefixer&lt;/a&gt; into springframework&lt;/p&gt;</description>
