                            <comment id="115729" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Sat, 16 May 2015 14:18:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the recent change to add a UriTemplateHandler might be a good fit. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-12750?focusedCommentId=115643&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-115643&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;comment here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="115733" author="pirkojm" created="Sat, 16 May 2015 22:20:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, the DefaultUriTemplateHandler can be the way. But the current implementation (as seen in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/commit/3e59c244f90c59aa98bed773cbae95416b591d36&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;code&lt;/a&gt; has no possibility to setup some  prefix, which is used for each request using restTemplate with such handler. To be exact, my point is not to have to use the same protocol://host:port/someapiprefix string in every URL I passes to restTemplate, but rather use URLs starting after that common prefix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can imagine to implement prefixing mechanism as UriTemplateHandler extending that Default one or simply add such functionality into the DefaultUriTemplateHandler. In addition I think this deserves to be implemented inside springframework - so if you agree I can code one of those variants.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you believe this usecase is too specific to be covered in framework, we can live with our implementation quite well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="115742" author="pirkojm" created="Sun, 17 May 2015 11:10:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, now I realized, you proposed to setup the prefix using UriTemplate for each request - yep it is definitely possible, but doesn&apos;t fit my usecase very well. (Developing client for API of specific vendor - so all my requests goes to the same host/prefix - so to setup host over and over doesn&apos;t help much). Hopefully now I clarified this thing better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="115813" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 12:02:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you provide an example of what URL do you want the code using the RestTemplate to pass and how it should be modified by the time the final URI is ready?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
